Cape Town â€“ A 17-year-old suspect is due to appear in the Wynberg Magistrate's Court today after being found in possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition. The teenager was arrested in Lavender Hill last night, said Western Cape police spokesperson Siyabulela Malo. Malo added that the teenager could be linked to a shooting incident, which policemen on patrol had been tipped off about and subsequently tracked down the suspect. "The policemen of SAPS Steenberg arrested a 17-year-old suspect who was found in possession of an unlicensed firearm with ammunition in Welton Road, Lavender Hill, last night at about 22:40. "Our observant members were busy conducting stop and search operations in the area when they were informed about a shooting incident. "The members responded and spotted an unknown man walking in the area. He was searched and found in possession of an unlicensed 9mm firearm with ammunition," Malo said. Cape Times